The speaker appears to have a lisp. There were some words spoken that were actual words, but due to the lisp sounded as if they were not "real" words. The word "legacy", for instance, is phonetically leh-gah-see but the speaker pronounces it as leh-gah-she with the H sound. The lisp makes it difficult to further distinguish between ASI and ASHI pronunciation.
